# How the foreign{} Block Works: Executing Python and Julia Inline

@meta {
  title: "How the foreign{}` Block Works: Executing Python and Julia Inline"
  date: "2026-04-03"
  author: "bad-antics"
  tags: ["foreign", "inline", "python", "julia"]
  reading_time: "10 min"
}

@heading level=1 {
  How the foreign{}` Block Works: Executing Python and Julia Inline
}

@paragraph {
  The foreign{}` block allows you to execute arbitrary code in other languages within your LATERALUS documents. In this post, we'll cover how it works, why it's useful, and some tips for using it effectively.
}

@code lang=lateralus {
  foreign python { 
    x = 5
    y = x + 3
    print(y)
  }
  
  foreign julia { 
    x = 5
    y = x + 2
    println(y)  
  }
}

@paragraph { ... }

@heading level=2 {
  Using foreign{} with Python
}

@paragraph { ... }

@code lang=lateralus {
  import math
  a = 5
  b = 7
  
  pi = 3.14
  c = a * pi
  
  def circle_area(a, b):
      return 3.14159 * (a**2)

  d = circle_area(10, 20)
  e = c / d
  
  print(e)
}
</script>
